        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 2:32PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 231 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Kearny, or over Harrison, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Jersey City and Hoboken around 235 PM EDT.
Ridgefield and Midtown Manhattan around 240 PM EDT.
Mott Haven and RFK Bridge around 245 PM EDT.
East Tremont and Laguardia Airport around 250 PM EDT.
Co-op City around 255 PM EDT.
Throgs Neck Bridge and City Island around 300 PM EDT.
New Rochelle around 305 PM EDT.
Sands Point around 310 PM EDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 8 PM.</instruction>
